    "name": "The Indigo",
    "profile": "Japanese pop group formed in 1998. Originally a trio, they played a mix of indie pop and soft rock. After bass player Kenichi Takagi left before the release of their third album, they gradually shifted from indie pop rock to slow ballads. They have performed a number of opening and ending songs for anime shows. This includes \"Namo Shirenu Hana\" (名も知れぬ花) for \"Ai Yori Aoshi,\" \"Under the Blue Sky\" for \"Someday's Dreamers,\" \"I Do!\" for Ai Yori Aoshi Enishi, and \"Fantasista Girl\" (ファンタジスタ★ガール) for \"Animal Yokocho.\"",
